<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <head>55. Telegram 389 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d55fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–1055. Official
                                Use Only.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-10">August 10, 1955, 5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d55-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d55-1"/>
                        <p>389. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Desire call attention FBIS item 091427 Peking International English
                            Service. This probably forecasts line <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> will take when “no force” reached and to which
                            reply some kind will be required.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>NOTE: Mr. Waddell’s office (FE) notified 8/10/55 4:37 p.m. EMB
                                CWO</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>